-- Shanghai to Publish PM2.5 Pollution Data by June, Chinanews Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-02-08T14:32:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/shanghai-to-publish-pm2-5-pollution-data-by-june-chinanews-says.html
Shanghai  will start publishing data
on pollutants smaller than 2.5 micrometers in diameter in June,
China News Service said today, citing Sun Jian, a deputy
director at the municipal environmental protection bureau.  The municipality plans to implement the China V grade for
car exhaust as early as next year to control emissions of small
particulates, according to  the report . China’s motor fuel
pollution standards are similar to the European Union’s; China V
gasoline is similar to Euro V.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
Chua Baizhen in Beijing at 
 bchua14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
